&gt;
&gt; I love the sense of humor Arthur shows tonight in his opening line!  ;-)
&gt; 
&gt; This is the 1:14 condensed version of a 2:18 session.  
&gt; 
&gt; Margaret
&gt; 
&gt; Is there anything you wanted to ask me tonight?
&gt; &quot;You are a beautiful human, however, you&#39;re dumb. L.M.O.&quot; OMG, he used internet 
slang!
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;m beautiful?
&gt; &quot;And dumb. But you love (me).&quot; The last word is very faint.
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;m in what? (still having trouble catching everything real-time)
&gt; &quot;L.A. Tech City&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; I heard you say the portals are open. What&#39;s a portal? (Heard in a previous session.)
&gt; &quot;They open and you humans talk for the interview portals.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; The portal is used for what?
&gt; &quot;Help you enter our air.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; To enter your air? Or your territory?
&gt; &quot;Air [groupie?] doubles air access. Air, I told you helps talk.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; The portal takes us to you?
&gt; &quot;Our elderly therapist, Arthur.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; What do you call our stations? If your stations are called an Air Port, what are ours 
called?
&gt; &quot;Air Portal U.F.O.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; Where am I? In your frame of reference, where am I?
&gt; &quot;You&#39;re here.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;m gonna listen again. Thanks Arthur.
&gt; &quot;I tell them hold access for you.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; Oh. One quick question. How do you close the portal?
&gt; &quot;You don&#39;t ever have to stop it. That helps out. I hold the answer. I have the air.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; OK, I&#39;m gonna listen.
&gt; &quot;Elders help. They&#39;ll give you air to us.&quot;
